<P>
   NY-AIRPORT-DENTIST (New York) _ Dr. Robert M. Trager is the man
with the unusual title of airport dentist and the unusual
responsibility of using dental and bone X-rays to determine an
immigrant's age, which can be critical to his or her effort to gain
entry to the United States. Hundreds of Chinese, Somalis, Sri
Lankans, Albanians, Hondurans and others who claim on travel
documents to be under 18 years old file through Trager's office and
get their teeth X-rayed, and then often their wrists. By Chris
Hedges.
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-DROUGHT (Throckmorton, Texas) _ In a state made rich and
famous by oil, there now is no more precious natural resource than
water. Reservoirs are at their third-lowest capacity in 23 years.
Small cities and metropolitan areas are in the full throes of water
conservation plans. The state usually suffers one drought every
decade, but this is the third drought in four years. By Jim
Yardley.
</P>
<P>
   (This article is tentative and may be eliminated later.)
