<P>
   &QL;  PA Contract Awards By Jimmy Chuang States News Service
Washington, July 21 -- Mark Electronics Inc. of Glenside won a
$63,291 contract from the Defense General Supply Center in
Richmond, Va., for aircraft components and accessories.
</P>
<P>
   U.S. Grove LLC of Chambersburg won a $83,713 contract from the
Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for vehicular equipment
components.
</P>
<P>
   Wheeler Brothers Inc. of Somerset won a $73,297 contract from
the Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for engine
accessories.
</P>
<P>
   Snap-Tite Hose Inc. of Union City won a $1.7 million contract
from the General Services Administration in Fort Worth, Texas, for
firefighting, rescue and safety equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Rhombic Systems of Yardley won a $197,708 contract from the U.S.
Naval Air Warfare Center in Patuxent River, Md., for research and
development.
</P>
<P>
   Renewal Inc. of Pittsburgh won a $2.94 million contract from the
Department of Justice in Washington for social services.
</P>
<P>
   Digital-Ink of Dillsburg won a $56,991 contract from the U.S.
Government Printing Office in Washington for photographic, mapping,
printing and publication services.
</P>
<P>
   VJ Supply Inc. of Broomall won a $61,625 contract from the
Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for pipe, tubing, hose and
fittings.
</P>
