   TEXAS-DROUGHT (Throckmorton, Texas) _ In a state made rich and
famous by oil, there now is no more precious natural resource than
water. Reservoirs are at their third-lowest capacity in 23 years.
Small cities and metropolitan areas are in the full throes of water
conservation plans. The state usually suffers one drought every
decade, but this is the third drought in four years. By Jim
Yardley.
