   BELGIAN-SHEEP (Warren, Vt.) _ A judge will decide Friday whether
to grant a reprieve to he 400 Vermont sheep, imported from
Belgium, that some fear may carry a sheep strain of mad cow
disease. A death sentence for the sheep could be a mortal blow to
the family cheese business run by Larry and Linda Falliace, who say
the worries about their flock are based on bad science. By Carey
Goldberg.
</P>
<P>
   NY-NILE-VIRUS (New York) _ The West Nile virus spreads: More
dead birds are found in Queens and on Staten Island, and mosquito
spraying will be expanded.
</P>
<P>
   NY-MOSQUITO-SPRAYING (New York) _ Mayor Rudolph Giuliani said
Friday that he would battle with the state and the federal
government, which are trying to limit the amount of mosquito
spraying. The state Department of Environmental Conservation is
worried about fish killed from pesticides in the wetlands, and the
federal government has numerous concerns. By Thomas Leuck.
</P>
