<P>
   WARNER-ON-WOOD _ Spalting, for those unfamiliar with the term,
refers to the fine dark lines, like ink drawings, that appear on
wood as insect activity and decay begins. It can happen on any
wood, but obviously is more pronounced on light woods such as
maple, beech and birch. (Warner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVED
