   RELIGIONATHEISM _ Atheists among us. Atheism is nothing new but
it's profile is rising and, since the days of McCarthy - when the
word was typically connected to ``communist'' and uttered with
contempt - so has its cache. Organizations like Schisler's that
meet on a regular basis to share ideas and discuss books (last
weeks was Losing Faith in Faith by Dan Barker) are popping up with
more frequency. The biggest boost in recent years to these
self-described independent iconoclasts? (Belkin, Palm Beach Post).
