<SLUG> BC-COKE-COFFEE22-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Coca-Cola to test cold, smoothie-like coffee drink
 &HT;    By Henry Unger
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Coca-Cola may be getting into the coffee business in
the United States.
</P>
<P>
   The company plans to start test marketing a cold, smoothie-type
coffee beverage next month in four U.S. markets.
</P>
<P>
   ``The company has repeatedly said that we're very actively
looking at developing a number of new, innovative beverage products
to drive our total beverage business,'' Coca-Cola spokeswoman Polly
Howes said Friday.
</P>
<P>
   While Coke sells ready-to-drink coffee beverages in other
countries, it doesn't have such a product here.
</P>
<P>
   Beverage Digest reported Friday that the coffee drink will be
called ``Cafielle.'' Coke's current focus is to sell the drink
through fountains _ not in bottles or cans, Beverage Digest said.
There are likely to be two flavors.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is a smart move,'' said John Sicher, Beverage Digest's
editor and publisher. ``The coffee beverage market in the U.S. is
still tiny and untapped, but could hold great potential.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
