<P>
   EPA-GRACE-ASBESTOS (Undated) _ The EPA is investigating why it
ignored evidence for 18 years that W.R. Grace and Co. produced ore
for its consumer products that was laden with asbestos. An agency
study in 1982 found alarming levels in material that Grace said was
virtually free of asbestos, but the agency shelved the report,
scuttled its planned follow-up studies and continued to accept the
company's lower figures, EPA officials say. Grace officials on
Friday did not dispute the EPA report, but said their own studies
have consistently shown much smaller amounts of asbestos. At issue
now is how much asbestos _ in a form known as tremolite _ made its
way into those products as a contaminant. By Michael Moss and
Adrianne Appel. (Scheduled to move by 9:30 p.m. ET in ``a'' news
