<P>
   (NYT26) RUSSIA -- July 21, 2000 --  ADV. FOR SUN. JULY 23 --
TV-COPS-RUSSIA -- In the last two years, St. Petersburgq has become
the hottest location for the hottest trend on Russian television:
gritty, tell-it-like-it-is cop shows. The boom began in early 1998
with "The Street of Broken Streetlights," a St. Petersburg version of
"Hill Street Blues." Now, in its wake, half a dozen mini-series are
being shot or are on the drawing boards in St. Petersburg, starring
counter-intelligence agents, mafia dons, tough female investigators
and other heroes and villains. From left, Yuri Petrenko, Aleksei
Nilov and the director Valery Naumov filming "The Street of Broken
Streetlights," in a rented St. Petersburg apartment. (James Hill/The
New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT25) VIENNA, Va. -- July 21, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN. JULY 23
-- VOTERS-SUBURBMOMS-COX --  In 1996, as they had in '92, a majority
of women voters handed Bill Clinton a decisive victory, demonstrating
their traditional preference for a Democrat over a Republican.
Catherine Browning, 41, mother of three from Vienna, Va., a suburb of
Washington, D.C., with her son Mark, 7, at a summer soccer camp.
Browning, a high school teacher, voted for Clinton in 1992 and 1996.
But she does not like Gore, and says she'll vote for third-party
candidate and consumer advocate Ralph Nader.  "I want authenticity.
Someone who is sculpted by some marketing specialist," she says. "I
just don't trust Gore because he seems so contradictory depending on
the audience he's talking to."  (Rick McKay/Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT24) SAN JOSE, Calif. -- July 21, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN.
JULY 23 -- INTERNET-HARDWARE-COX-2 -- At its physical core, the
Internet is vast network of copper wires and optical fibers.
Shuttling packets of data across these "pipes" to their proper
destinations are tens of thousands of special-purpose computers known
as routers, all programmed with same protocol, or addressing
language. Backing up those machines are simplified routers, known as
switchers. This Cisco Systems' 12000-series unit is widely used by
large Internet providers. (Cox News service)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT23) SAN JOSE, Calif. -- July 21, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN.
JULY 23 -- INTERNET-HARDWARE-COX-1 --  Cisco Systems Inc., a Silicon
Valley hardware giant has a current valuation of some $460 billion.
Cisco, which sells its products in some 115 countries, enjoys an
effective lock on the world's high-speed data networks. The sprawling
headquaters of Cisco Systems, Inc.  of San Jose, Ca. (Cox News
Service)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT22) NEAR WACO, Texas -- July 21, 2000 -- WACO-REPORT-2 --
The blame for the catastrophe at Waco that killed 80 people in 1993
rests solely with cult leader David Koresh, former Sen. John Danforth
said Friday after a 10-month independent investigation. An American
and Arkansas flag flank a memorial stone near the site of the former
Branch Davidian compound in honor of four agents with the Bureau of
Alcohol, Tobacco and Firearms who were killed in 1993 during the
botched raid on the compound. (Rod Aydelotte/Waco Tribune Herald)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT21) NEAR WACO, Texas -- July 21, 2000 -- WACO-REPORT --
