<P>
   (NYT20) NEW YORK -- July 21, 2000 -- SUB-NY-POLICE-FUNERAL --
Thousands of officers stood in a solemn chain of sorrow outside a
Staten Island church Friday to say a final goodbye to Officer John
Kelly, who was killed in a car wreck while chasing a motorcycle
thief. Mourners wepT following funeral services at Our Lady Star of
the Sea Catholic church, Friday.  The 31-year-old Kelly, whose three
brothers and wife are also police officers, died Monday after his
unmarked patrol car crashed into a utility pole in the Bloomfield
section of Staten Island. (Andrea Mohin/The New York Times) This
previous listing.
